  "prompt": "Did any of Melania Trump's family come to her wedding? Did anyone \"give her away?\" And who paid for her wedding gown?",
  "response": "Melania Trump's wedding to Donald Trump took place on January 22, 2005, at Bethesda-by-the-Sea Episcopal Church in Palm Beach, Florida. Here are the details regarding your specific questions:\n\n1. **Family Attendance:** Yes, members of Melania's family attended the wedding. Her parents, Amalija and Viktor Knavs, were present at the ceremony.\n\n2. **Who Gave Her Away:** Melania was escorted down the aisle by her father, Viktor Knavs, who \"gave her away\" during the wedding ceremony.\n\n3. **Wedding Gown Payment:** Melania's wedding gown was a custom creation by Dior, designed by John Galliano. It is reported that Donald Trump paid for the gown, which reportedly cost around $100,000.\n\nThese details highlight some of the key aspects of their wedding, which was a lavish affair attended by many high-profile guests.",
